quran[12]{c,v,t,f}:
  36,67,"And if it had been Our Will, We could have transformed them (into animals or lifeless objects) in their places. Then they would have been unable to go forward (move about) nor they could have turned back.{1}",footnotes:1:{36:67} See {7:166} and the footnote of {5:90}.
  36,68,"And he whom We grant long life - We reverse him in creation (weakness after strength). Will they not then understand?"
  36,69,"And We have not taught him (Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم) poetry, nor is it suitable for him. This is only a Reminder and a plain Qur’ân."
  37,52,"Who used to say: "
  37,53,""
  37,54,"(The speaker) said: "
  38,31,"When there were displayed before him, in the afternoon, well trained horses of the highest breed [for Jihâd (holy fighting in Allâh’s Cause)]."
  38,32,"He said: "
  38,33,"Then he said "
  39,16,"They shall have coverings of Fire, above them and covering (of Fire) beneath them. With this Allâh does frighten His slaves: "
  39,17,"Those who avoid At-Tâghût {1} (false deities) by not worshipping them and turn to Allâh (in repentance), for them are glad tidings; so announce the good news to My slaves -",footnotes:1:{39:17} See the footnote of {2:256}.
  39,18,"Those who listen to the Word [good advice Lâ ilâha illallâh - (none has the right to be worshipped but Allâh) and Islâmic Monotheism] and follow the best thereof (i.e. worship Allâh Alone, repent to Him and avoid Tâghût) those are (the ones) whom Allâh has guided and those are men of understanding.{1}",footnotes:1:{39:18} Like Zaid bin ‘Amr bin Nufail, Salmân Al-Fârisi and Abû Dharr Al-Ghifârî. [Tafsir Al- Qurtubi, also see the footnote of (Verse 2:135)].